rComments: This is the easiest class I've ever taken. No need to even attend lecture!!!
He has made improvements from the first semester he taught the subject: he no longer writes his own problems, but his tests and quizzes are still very time restrictive, but the material was fair.

Although he emphasizes neatness and clarity, his board problems are anything but that.  He also thinks his homework is "easy," yet when I went to his office hours, it seems he struggled on figuring out his own homework problems.  Not sure what others thought of him, but I would look at another professor before taking him.
